summary:
• Director Trading Disclosure: Jason Boyes (Director & CEO of Infratil Limited) acquired 45,393 IFT ordinary shares on-market between 7-Jul-25 and 11-Jul-25 at prices ranging from NZ$10.92251 to NZ$10.9584 per share.
  • Total consideration: ~NZ$497,329.75.
  • Post-transaction holdings: 2,427,830 shares (beneficially owned).

No material impact on capital structure or liquidity identified.

Capital Raising Announcement

  • Structure: Placement + Share Purchase Plan (SPP)
  • Placement: AUD $16.1 million raised (oversubscribed) at $0.10/share (18% premium to 20-day VWAP).
  • SPP: AUD $5 million targeted (potential oversubscription); retail shareholders eligible.
  • Key Dates:
  • Annual Meeting: 6 August 2025 (shareholder approval for placement required).
  • SPP Opening: Mid-July 2025 (conditional on placement approval).

Operational Highlights (Q1 FY26)

  • US Test Volumes:
  • Total Laboratory Throughput (TLT): 6,900 tests (down 8.9% QoQ).
  • US TLT: 5,717 tests (down 11.9% QoQ) due to transition from Detect to Triage.
  • Triage adoption: 77% of US tests in June 2025 (vs. 22% in Q4 FY25).
  • Asia Pacific Growth: 1,183 tests (up 8.8% QoQ).
  • Medicare Reconsideration: Positive discussions with Novitas; reconsideration request submitted for Triage (based on AUA Guideline inclusion and STRATA study).

Material Developments

  1. Triage Plus Progress:
  2. Analytical Validation published (Diagnostics, July 2025); supports Medicare reconsideration.
  3. Draft Medicare price: US$1,018/test (vs. $760 for Triage). Pending DRIVE study peer review (submitted June 2025).
  4. AUA Guideline Impact:
  5. Triage holds "Grade A" evidence rating; drives payer negotiations (e.g., Optum VACCN coverage at Medicare rate).
  6. Cash Runway: Capital raise extends runway >12 months without Medicare coverage.

Omitted: Routine details on director re-elections, clinical study timelines (non-near-term), and regional breakdowns.
Key Focus: Capital structure, volume trends, Medicare strategy, and Triage Plus commercialization.

• Announcement Type: Employee incentive scheme securities issuance
  • Securities Issued: 192,360 ordinary fully paid shares (ASX: SNZ)
  • Issue Price: NZD 11.8757 per share
  • Issue Date: 14/07/2025
  • Ranking: Equally with existing shares
  • Post-Issue Issued Capital: 241,123,378 ordinary shares on issue
  • Key Management Personnel (KMP) Allocations:
  • Scott Scoullar: 84 shares
  • Margaret Warrington: 84 shares

No material impact on capital structure or liquidity expected (minor issuance under incentive scheme).
